&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the proactive and enthusiastic Early Supported Discharge Team based at Blackpool Football Stadium. The post is to cover winter pressures until March 2021&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will work as a member of the multi disciplinary team supporting in the delivery of rehabilitation within patient&#39;s homes along the Fylde Coast..&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will work collaboratively with others and support members of the team in the delivery of rehabilitation for a wide range of health conditions,&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will have experience of working collaboratively within a community or acute setting. The post-holder will have excellent assessment, and intervention skills. You will be able to carry out comprehensive assessments and make autonomous decisions based on the data obtained. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The role requires good communication skills and an ability to work as an effective member of a multi-disciplinary nurse led team as well as with other external agencies. A high level of inter-professional working exists in the Early Supported Discharge Team giving the opportunity for you to develop and transfer your clinical skills. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The service operates from 08.30-16.30 over 7 days. Car driver essential. .&lt;/p&gt;
